WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.733 --> 00:00:10.933
Narrator: IN THIS WORLD.
THERE IS REAL EVIL

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.233
IN THE DARKEST SHADOWS
AND IN THE MOST ORDINARY PLACES.

3
00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:18.733
THESE ARE THE TRUE STORIES
OF THE INNOCENT

4
00:00:18.800 --> 00:00:20.733
AND THE UNIMAGINABLE.

5
00:00:23.167 --> 00:00:26.200
CINDY SARROW AND HER FAMILY
MOVED BACK TO HER HOMETOWN.

6
00:00:26.267 --> 00:00:27.967
HOPING FOR A BETTER LIFE.

7
00:00:29.433 --> 00:00:32.400
BUT SOMETHING SINISTER
LURKS IN THE SHADOWS.

8
00:00:32.467 --> 00:00:34.200
WAITING TO MAKE ITS MOVE.

9
00:00:35.167 --> 00:00:36.900
DESPERATE
TO PROTECT HER CHILDREN

10
00:00:36.967 --> 00:00:39.200
FROM SOMETHING SHE CANNOT SEE...

11
00:00:40.533 --> 00:00:43.567
...SHE BECOMES CAUGHT
IN A SUPERNATURAL NIGHTMARE

12
00:00:43.633 --> 00:00:45.333
SHE CANNOT ESCAPE.

13
00:00:47.233 --> 00:00:49.467
[ WHISPERING ]

14
00:00:49.533 --> 00:00:54.367
BETWEEN THE WORLD WE SEE
AND THE THINGS WE FEAR.

15
00:00:54.433 --> 00:00:56.633
THERE ARE DOORS.

16
00:00:56.700 --> 00:00:59.333
WHEN THEY ARE OPENED...

17
00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:03.267
NIGHTMARES BECOME REALITY.

18
00:01:11.233 --> 00:01:13.233
EVEN THE MOST INNOCUOUS PLACES

19
00:01:13.300 --> 00:01:16.533
BEAR THE SCARS
OF A TWISTED PAST.

20
00:01:16.600 --> 00:01:20.100
EVIL CAN ECHO THROUGH TIME.

21
00:01:20.167 --> 00:01:24.200
LYING DORMANT
UNTIL THE UNSUSPECTING

22
00:01:24.267 --> 00:01:26.633
AND THE ILL-PREPARED

23
00:01:26.700 --> 00:01:29.933
UNKNOWINGLY CROSS ITS PATH.

24
00:01:40.467 --> 00:01:43.533
ON THE OUTSKIRTS OF ST. LOUIS

25
00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:46.633
SITS THE TOWNSHIP
OF BELLEVILLE. ILLINOIS.

26
00:01:46.700 --> 00:01:51.267
LIKE MANY SMALL CITIES AND TOWNS
THAT DOT THE MIDWEST LANDSCAPE.

27
00:01:51.333 --> 00:01:54.200
IT HAS REMAINED THE SAME
FOR DECADES.

28
00:01:57.633 --> 00:02:00.833
THE YEAR IS 1991.

29
00:02:04.433 --> 00:02:06.767
34-YEAR-OLD CINDY SARROW

30
00:02:06.833 --> 00:02:10.067
HAS LIVED IN THE SMALL TOWN
FOR THE PAST TWO YEARS.

31
00:02:12.633 --> 00:02:18.900
TONIGHT. CINDY CAN'T SHAKE THE
FEELING THAT SOMETHING IS WRONG.

32
00:02:40.433 --> 00:02:43.100
[ GROWL ]

33
00:02:51.967 --> 00:02:55.233
[ GROWLING ]

34
00:03:08.967 --> 00:03:10.333
[ DOG BARKING ]

35
00:03:16.867 --> 00:03:19.633
[ GROWLING ]

36
00:03:38.867 --> 00:03:40.833
[ STAIRS CREAK ]

37
00:03:41.900 --> 00:03:43.667
[ SCREAMS ]

38
00:03:48.267 --> 00:03:51.500
Cindy: I JUST THOUGHT
IT WAS A NIGHTMARE.

39
00:03:51.567 --> 00:03:54.833
BUT THEN I KEPT HAVING IT OVER
AND OVER -- THE SAME DREAM.

40
00:04:01.100 --> 00:04:05.467
IN MY DREAMS.
I WAS FEARING FOR MY LIFE.

41
00:04:05.533 --> 00:04:11.200
AND I KNEW THAT WHATEVER THIS
WAS WAS TRYING TO KILL ME.

42
00:04:11.267 --> 00:04:12.700
I JUST FELT IT.

43
00:04:31.933 --> 00:04:33.767
HERE YOU GO. HONEY.

44
00:04:33.833 --> 00:04:35.367
WHAT DO YOU THINK THE SURPRISE
WILL BE?

45
00:04:35.433 --> 00:04:38.500
Narrator:
CINDY IS AT STAY-AT-HOME MOM.

46
00:04:38.567 --> 00:04:40.333
SHE HAS TWO CHILDREN --

47
00:04:40.400 --> 00:04:43.667
7-YEAR-OLD CHRISTIE
AND 9-YEAR-OLD BROOKE.

48
00:04:43.733 --> 00:04:46.233
Brooke: ME AND MY FAMILY
ARE REALLY CLOSE.

49
00:04:46.300 --> 00:04:48.367
AND IT SEEMED THAT NOTHING
COULD TEAR US APART.

50
00:04:48.433 --> 00:04:51.733
WHEN'S DADDY GONNA GET HERE?
HE'S TAKING FOREVER.

51
00:04:51.800 --> 00:04:54.200
HE'LL BE HERE
IN JUST A FEW MINUTES.

52
00:04:54.267 --> 00:04:56.667
HONEY. RELAX
AND EAT YOUR BREAKFAST.

53
00:04:56.733 --> 00:04:57.733
I CAN'T.

54
00:04:57.800 --> 00:05:00.900
I'M TOO EXCITED
ABOUT THE SURPRISE.

55
00:05:00.967 --> 00:05:02.400
WHAT DO YOU THINK IT IS?

56
00:05:02.467 --> 00:05:05.467
I HAVE NO IDEA.

57
00:05:05.533 --> 00:05:07.667
BUT I BET WHATEVER IT IS.
IT'S WONDERFUL.

58
00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:09.933
DAD'S HOME.

59
00:05:10.067 --> 00:05:13.067
Narrator: CINDY'S
LONGTIME BOYFRIEND. JAKE.

60
00:05:13.100 --> 00:05:15.700
WORKS THE GRAVEYARD SHIFT AT
A CHEMICAL PLANT IN ST. LOUIS.

61
00:05:15.767 --> 00:05:17.767
HOW ARE MY LITTLE LADIES
TODAY. HMM?

62
00:05:17.833 --> 00:05:19.633
[ SMOOCHES ]

63
00:05:19.700 --> 00:05:21.067
HEY.

64
00:05:21.133 --> 00:05:22.233
HI. HONEY.

65
00:05:24.567 --> 00:05:26.867
EVERYONE READY
FOR MY BIG SURPRISE?

66
00:05:26.933 --> 00:05:28.233
WHAT IS IT?

67
00:05:28.300 --> 00:05:30.500
WELL. YOU KNOW
HOW WE'VE BEEN WANTING

68
00:05:30.567 --> 00:05:32.500
TO MOVE BACK TO CASEYVILLE.

69
00:05:32.567 --> 00:05:35.567
CLOSER TO YOUR MOTHER.
CLOSER TO WORK FOR ME?

70
00:05:37.667 --> 00:05:39.133
WHAT IS IT?

71
00:05:39.200 --> 00:05:41.500
TELL US. DADDY!
WHAT'S THE BIG SURPRISE?

72
00:05:41.567 --> 00:05:42.900
GIRLS...

73
00:05:44.167 --> 00:05:46.067
GO GET DRESSED
AND I'LL SHOW YOU.

74
00:05:50.333 --> 00:05:52.700
I THINK...

75
00:05:52.767 --> 00:05:54.533
I THINK I FOUND
THAT DREAM HOME.

76
00:05:58.967 --> 00:06:02.200
Narrator: BOTH CINDY AND JAKE
GREW UP IN CASEYVILLE.

77
00:06:02.267 --> 00:06:05.767
A RURAL TOWN AT THE BASE
OF THE MISSISSIPPI RIVER BLUFFS.

78
00:06:11.600 --> 00:06:15.100
FOR MONTHS. THEY'VE TALKED ABOUT
MOVING BACK TO THEIR HOMETOWN

79
00:06:15.167 --> 00:06:17.833
AND RAISING THEIR FAMILY THERE.

80
00:06:19.233 --> 00:06:20.600
UH-HUH.

81
00:06:20.667 --> 00:06:23.800
COME ON!
HOP TO!

82
00:06:34.133 --> 00:06:36.867
BE CAREFUL. YOU TWO!

83
00:06:36.933 --> 00:06:38.367
SO.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

84
00:06:38.433 --> 00:06:40.167
IT'S NICE.

85
00:06:40.233 --> 00:06:42.333
I REALLY LIKE IT.

86
00:06:42.400 --> 00:06:45.567
BUT DO WE HAVE THE MONEY
FOR A PLACE LIKE THIS?

87
00:06:45.633 --> 00:06:46.833
BARELY. BUT. YES.

88
00:06:46.900 --> 00:06:49.333
IT WAS A HOUSE
THAT WE COULD AFFORD.

89
00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:51.700
BUT WE WERE REALLY
FINANCIALLY STRAPPED.

90
00:06:51.767 --> 00:06:54.667
THERE WAS THINGS THAT NEEDED
TO BE DONE TO THE HOUSE.

91
00:06:54.733 --> 00:06:57.833
WE WOULD HAVE TO COME UP WITH
THE MONEY FOR THAT.

92
00:06:57.900 --> 00:07:01.567
SOUNDS LIKE IT'S GONNA TAKE A
LOT OF MONEY AND A LOT OF WORK.

93
00:07:01.633 --> 00:07:03.400
I KNOW. HONEY. I KNOW.

94
00:07:03.467 --> 00:07:06.100
BUT THERE AREN'T A LOT OF HOUSES
UP FOR SALE RIGHT NOW.

95
00:07:06.167 --> 00:07:09.067
AND IT MIGHT BE YEARS BEFORE
WE GET ANOTHER CHANCE LIKE THIS.

96
00:07:09.100 --> 00:07:10.900
NOW. YOU'VE ALWAYS
TALKED ABOUT

97
00:07:10.967 --> 00:07:13.533
HOW MUCH YOU'VE WANTED
TO RAISE OUR FAMILY HERE.

98
00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:16.967
IT REALLY IS
A GREAT HOUSE.

99
00:07:17.067 --> 00:07:18.900
IT IS A GREAT HOUSE.

100
00:07:18.967 --> 00:07:21.167
YEAH?
ALL RIGHT!

101
00:07:21.233 --> 00:07:22.167
[ LAUGHS ]

102
00:07:22.233 --> 00:07:25.067
WE WERE REAL EXCITED.

103
00:07:25.133 --> 00:07:26.267
WE WEREN'T RENTING.

104
00:07:26.333 --> 00:07:28.800
WE'D HAVE OUR OWN HOME
AND JUST BE HAPPY.

105
00:07:28.867 --> 00:07:30.600
ISN'T THAT GREAT?

106
00:07:30.667 --> 00:07:31.800
ALL RIGHT?

107
00:07:31.867 --> 00:07:35.433
WE CAN FIT OUR TV
RIGHT THROUGH THERE.

108
00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:49.600
MOM!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

109
00:07:49.667 --> 00:07:50.933
Narrator: CINDY IS GRATEFUL

110
00:07:51.067 --> 00:07:53.200
TO BE NEAR
HER AILING MOTHER. ANITA.

111
00:07:53.267 --> 00:07:55.733
WHO SUFFERS
FROM A DEGENERATIVE DISEASE.

112
00:07:55.800 --> 00:07:59.067
Cindy: SHE WAS SICK.
AND SHE WAS GETTING SICKER.

113
00:07:59.133 --> 00:08:01.400
AND I JUST WANTED
TO BE CLOSE TO HER

114
00:08:01.467 --> 00:08:04.433
TO BE ABLE TO HELP HER
AND BE WITH HER.

115
00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:07.700
GRANDMA'S HERE!
GRANDMA!

116
00:08:07.767 --> 00:08:09.233
OH. SO GOOD TO SEE YOU!

117
00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:10.800
WANT TO SEE MY NEW ROOM?

118
00:08:10.867 --> 00:08:13.433
OUR NEW ROOM.
SURE.

119
00:08:13.500 --> 00:08:15.300
GIRLS. TAKE GRANDMA INSIDE.
OKAY.

120
00:08:22.367 --> 00:08:24.300
I'LL GET THE REST
OF THE BOXES.

121
00:08:24.367 --> 00:08:26.067
YOU SHOULD START UNPACKING.

122
00:08:26.067 --> 00:08:27.267
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.

123
00:08:27.333 --> 00:08:29.367
THANKS. HONEY.

124
00:08:37.167 --> 00:09:45.267
[ CABINET DOOR SQUEAKS ]

125
00:09:45.333 --> 00:09:47.067
JAKE!

126
00:09:50.133 --> 00:09:53.300
THE CABINET DOORS
ARE FALLING OFF!

127
00:09:53.367 --> 00:09:55.300
I THINK IT'S JUST THE HINGES
ON THESE DOORS

128
00:09:55.367 --> 00:09:56.800
ARE JUST A LITTLE TOO OLD.

129
00:09:56.867 --> 00:09:59.233
Cindy:
I HAD DOUBTS ABOUT THE HOUSE.

130
00:09:59.300 --> 00:10:01.500
I THOUGHT.
"WHAT DID I BUY HERE?"

131
00:10:01.567 --> 00:10:02.967
I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

132
00:10:03.033 --> 00:10:05.933
I SHOULD EXPECT THINGS LIKE THIS
TO HAPPEN.

133
00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:08.000
IT IS
A PRETTY OLD HOUSE.

134
00:10:08.067 --> 00:10:09.133
EXACTLY.

135
00:10:09.200 --> 00:10:11.833
NOW. WHERE DID I PUT
MY TOOLS?

136
00:10:24.967 --> 00:10:27.200
Narrator: THAT NIGHT.

137
00:10:27.267 --> 00:10:30.367
CINDY HELPS HER DAUGHTERS
SET UP THEIR NEW ROOM.

138
00:10:44.400 --> 00:10:47.067
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLING ]

139
00:11:03.567 --> 00:11:08.067
OH. LOOKS LIKE THAT BULB'S
ABOUT TO GO.

140
00:11:08.067 --> 00:11:10.700
HOLD ON. GIRLS. WHILE I GO
LOOK FOR ANOTHER LIGHT BULB.

141
00:11:15.567 --> 00:11:19.933
THE BEDROOM HAD
A VERY EERIE FEELING TO IT.

142
00:11:23.333 --> 00:11:25.067
I JUST HAD A HORRIBLE FEELING

143
00:11:25.067 --> 00:11:27.500
THAT SOMETHING WAS WRONG
WITH THE HOUSE.

144
00:11:27.567 --> 00:11:29.133
[ CRACKLING CONTINUES ]

145
00:11:38.667 --> 00:11:41.100
WHOA. WHERE ARE YOU
RUNNING OFF TO?

146
00:11:41.167 --> 00:11:43.200
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

147
00:11:43.267 --> 00:11:45.133
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

148
00:11:45.200 --> 00:11:48.433
'CAUSE I WASN'T SURE MYSELF
ABOUT WHAT WAS GOING ON --

149
00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:51.467
WE HAD JUST MOVED THERE --
THAT I DIDN'T WANT TO WORRY HER.

150
00:11:51.533 --> 00:11:53.633
IT'S OKAY. HONEY.
YOU CAN TELL ME.

151
00:11:53.700 --> 00:11:55.167
I DON'T LIKE MY ROOM. MOM.

152
00:11:55.233 --> 00:11:57.800
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
IT'S A GREAT ROOM.

153
00:11:57.867 --> 00:11:59.600
IT'S PERFECT FOR YOU GUYS.

154
00:11:59.667 --> 00:12:00.700
I DON'T KNOW.

155
00:12:00.767 --> 00:12:02.633
THERE'S SOMETHING CREEPY
ABOUT IT.

156
00:12:02.700 --> 00:12:04.767
I CAN'T SLEEP IN THERE.

157
00:12:04.833 --> 00:12:06.800
I DON'T WANT TO SLEEP IN THERE.
EITHER.

158
00:12:06.867 --> 00:12:08.433
OH. YOU GUYS
DON'T HAVE TO BE SCARED.

159
00:12:08.500 --> 00:12:10.367
YOUR FATHER AND I WILL BE
RIGHT HERE WITH YOU.

160
00:12:10.433 --> 00:12:11.400
MOM. NO!

161
00:12:11.467 --> 00:12:12.800
BROOKE!

162
00:12:12.867 --> 00:12:14.633
YOU ARE TOO OLD
TO BE ACTING LIKE THIS.

163
00:12:14.700 --> 00:12:16.767
I EXPECT MORE FROM YOU.

164
00:12:16.833 --> 00:12:19.067
BUT. DADDY --
NO "BUTS." OKAY?

165
00:12:19.067 --> 00:12:22.367
NOW. THAT'S WHERE YOU GIRLS
ARE SLEEPING. AND THAT'S FINAL.

166
00:12:23.833 --> 00:12:25.267
CAN YOU DO IT FOR ME?

167
00:12:25.333 --> 00:12:28.333
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY. I'LL DO IT.

168
00:12:28.400 --> 00:12:30.167
Jake: THAT'S MY GIRL.

169
00:12:32.367 --> 00:12:34.800
THANK YOU. HONEY.

170
00:12:39.567 --> 00:12:41.667
Narrator:
LATER THAT NIGHT...

171
00:12:50.067 --> 00:12:53.133
...AS IF SEEING HER HOUSE
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

172
00:12:53.200 --> 00:12:56.267
CINDY HAS A SUDDEN REVELATION.

173
00:12:56.333 --> 00:12:58.800
Cindy;
I COULDN'T BELIEVE IT.

174
00:12:58.867 --> 00:13:02.800
IT WAS THE SAME STAIRS
THAT ARE IN MY NIGHTMARES.

175
00:13:05.433 --> 00:13:08.800
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

176
00:13:19.100 --> 00:13:24.233
I WAS REALLY AFRAID.
BUT WHAT COULD I DO?

177
00:13:24.300 --> 00:13:27.367
Narrator: CINDY KNOWS THAT JAKE
WOULD NEVER CONSIDER MOVING

178
00:13:27.433 --> 00:13:29.733
BECAUSE OF AN EERIE FEELING.

179
00:13:34.967 --> 00:13:37.333
[ GASPS ]

180
00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:39.333
YOU OKAY?

181
00:13:39.400 --> 00:13:40.967
LOOK LIKE
YOU'VE SEEN A GHOST.

182
00:13:41.067 --> 00:13:42.400
YEAH. I'M OKAY.

183
00:13:42.467 --> 00:13:45.300
JUST A LITTLE TIRED.
THAT'S ALL.

184
00:13:45.367 --> 00:13:46.567
ALL RIGHT.

185
00:13:46.633 --> 00:13:48.133
YOU READY FOR WORK?

186
00:13:48.200 --> 00:13:49.133
YEAH.

187
00:13:49.200 --> 00:13:50.767
IN FACT.
I'M A LITTLE LATE.

188
00:13:50.833 --> 00:13:53.400
DO YOU THINK MAYBE
YOU COULD PLAY HOOKY?

189
00:13:53.467 --> 00:13:56.167
YOU KNOW. MAYBE CALL IN SICK
OR SOMETHING?

190
00:13:56.233 --> 00:13:58.467
WHAT. YOU GETTING
FREAKED OUT. TOO?

191
00:13:58.533 --> 00:14:00.067
IT'S NO WONDER
BROOKE AND CHRISTIE

192
00:14:00.067 --> 00:14:01.467
DON'T WANT TO SLEEP
IN THEIR ROOM.

193
00:14:01.533 --> 00:14:03.367
LIKE MOTHER.
LIKE DAUGHTERS.

194
00:14:03.433 --> 00:14:05.367
YOU'LL BE OKAY.
ALL RIGHT?

195
00:14:05.433 --> 00:14:06.600
[ SMOOCHES ]

196
00:14:06.667 --> 00:14:09.867
IF YOU NEED ME.
GIVE ME A CALL AT WORK.

197
00:14:09.933 --> 00:14:13.400
IF YOU DON'T.
I'LL SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

198
00:14:13.467 --> 00:14:15.067
OKAY.

199
00:14:47.633 --> 00:14:50.967
Brooke: IT SEEMED LIKE
EVERY HOUR. I WAS WAKING UP.

200
00:14:53.967 --> 00:14:57.733
I HAD THIS FEELING
THAT SOMEONE WAS THERE.

201
00:14:57.800 --> 00:15:50.700
WATCHING ME.
BUT I COULDN'T SEE ANYONE.

202
00:15:50.767 --> 00:15:52.500
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

203
00:15:57.233 --> 00:15:59.300
Narrator:
A FEW WEEKS LATER.

204
00:15:59.367 --> 00:16:03.067
CINDY FINALLY BEGINS TO FEEL
SETTLED IN HER NEW HOME.

205
00:16:18.533 --> 00:16:20.900
COME ON. GIRLS.

206
00:16:20.967 --> 00:16:22.533
YOU HAVE YOUR OWN BEDS.

207
00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:25.067
WHY DON'T YOU
SLEEP IN OUR ROOM?

208
00:16:25.100 --> 00:16:27.400
BECAUSE YOUR BED'S
TOO SMALL.

209
00:16:27.467 --> 00:16:28.667
NOW. COME ON. LET'S GO.

210
00:16:28.733 --> 00:16:31.567
BUT. MOM. I CAN'T.
PLEASE.

211
00:16:31.633 --> 00:16:33.400
I COULDN'T GO BACK IN THERE.

212
00:16:33.467 --> 00:16:36.067
I COULDN'T SLEEP IN THERE.
I WAS AFRAID. REALLY.

213
00:16:36.100 --> 00:16:38.233
I THINK THAT'S WHAT IT
COMES DOWN TO --

214
00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:39.633
I WAS JUST REALLY AFRAID.

215
00:16:39.700 --> 00:16:42.933
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL SLEEP ON THE SOFA.

216
00:16:43.067 --> 00:16:46.533
BUT SOONER OR LATER.
THIS HAS GOT TO END.

217
00:16:46.600 --> 00:16:48.633
GOOD NIGHT.
GOOD NIGHT. MOM.

218
00:16:48.700 --> 00:16:51.233
GOOD NIGHT. BABY.

219
00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:57.400
SLEEP TIGHT.

220
00:17:29.833 --> 00:17:32.667
[ CREAKING ]

221
00:17:52.100 --> 00:17:54.967
[ CREAKING ]

222
00:18:01.167 --> 00:18:04.767
[ CREAKING ]

223
00:18:04.833 --> 00:18:06.700
Narrator:
CINDY FEARS THAT SOMEONE

224
00:18:06.767 --> 00:18:09.067
MAY HAVE BROKEN INTO THE HOUSE.

225
00:18:11.667 --> 00:18:14.600
Cindy: I WAS AFRAID
FOR MY CHILDREN AND MYSELF

226
00:18:14.667 --> 00:18:17.800
BECAUSE WE WERE HOME
BY OURSELVES.

227
00:19:11.267 --> 00:19:13.333
MOM?
[ GASPS ]

228
00:19:14.833 --> 00:19:16.200
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

229
00:19:16.267 --> 00:19:19.067
HONEY.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP?

230
00:19:19.100 --> 00:19:20.467
I WAS THIRSTY.

231
00:19:20.533 --> 00:19:21.667
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

232
00:19:21.733 --> 00:19:24.500
I THOUGHT I HEARD
A NOISE.

233
00:19:24.567 --> 00:19:26.600
YOU REALLY SCARED ME.

234
00:19:26.667 --> 00:19:29.567
I KNOW. YOU JUMPED
LIKE 10 FEET IN THE AIR.

235
00:19:29.633 --> 00:19:33.233
ALL RIGHT.
NOW YOU NEED TO GET TO BED.

236
00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:34.900
NIGHT. MOM.

237
00:19:44.767 --> 00:19:47.067
Narrator:
THE FOLLOWING NIGHT.

238
00:19:47.067 --> 00:19:50.800
CINDY CALLS HER MOTHER. ANITA.
TO SEE HOW SHE'S FEELING.

239
00:19:50.867 --> 00:19:54.633
SHE LIVES IN A ONE-BEDROOM
APARTMENT ACROSS TOWN.

240
00:19:54.700 --> 00:19:56.600
Anita:
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

241
00:19:56.667 --> 00:19:59.067
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN.
MY HEAD STARTED TO SPIN.

242
00:19:59.133 --> 00:20:01.133
SHOULD I STOP BY
YOUR PLACE?

243
00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:04.367
I appreciate the offer.
but don't bother. honey.

244
00:20:04.433 --> 00:20:07.567
I THINK WHAT I NEED
IS JUST TO REST FOR A WHILE.

245
00:20:07.633 --> 00:20:09.167
OKAY. SOUNDS GOOD.

246
00:20:09.233 --> 00:20:12.300
WELL. I GUESS
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

247
00:20:12.367 --> 00:20:14.333
OKAY. SURE.

248
00:20:16.000 --> 00:20:19.067
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

249
00:20:19.133 --> 00:20:24.100
MOM. I THINK
THAT THE HOUSE IS...

250
00:20:24.167 --> 00:20:26.233
[ STATIC HISSES ]

251
00:20:28.400 --> 00:20:30.100
CINDY?

252
00:20:30.167 --> 00:21:10.367
LOOK. MOM. EVERYTHING'S FINE.
I GOT TO GO.

253
00:21:10.433 --> 00:21:14.300
Narrator: WITH ALL THE STRANGE
THINGS OCCURRING IN THE HOUSE...

254
00:21:19.867 --> 00:21:23.100
...CINDY BEGINS
TO HAVE TROUBLE SLEEPING.

255
00:21:39.500 --> 00:21:41.500
[ SCREAMS ]

256
00:21:41.567 --> 00:21:42.633
[ GASPS ]

257
00:21:42.700 --> 00:21:45.133
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

258
00:21:50.700 --> 00:21:52.600
I COULDN'T GO BLACK TO SLEEP

259
00:21:52.667 --> 00:21:56.267
BECAUSE I JUST FELT THERE WAS
SOMEBODY STARING AT ME.

260
00:21:56.333 --> 00:21:59.900
I KNEW SOMEBODY WAS THERE.
BUT I COULDN'T SEE THEM.

261
00:22:00.067 --> 00:22:03.267
I COULD JUST FEEL
THEIR PRESENCE.

262
00:22:09.067 --> 00:22:11.800
Narrator:
THE NEXT MORNING.

263
00:22:24.200 --> 00:22:26.800
Cindy: I WAS PUSHED SO HARD
THAT I WENT DOWN.

264
00:22:39.467 --> 00:22:43.867
Narrator: CINDY IS HESITANT
TO TELL JAKE WHAT JUST HAPPENED.

265
00:22:43.933 --> 00:22:46.700
SHE CAN BARELY BELIEVE IT
HERSELF.

266
00:22:57.567 --> 00:22:59.367
JAKE?

267
00:22:59.433 --> 00:23:00.667
WAKE UP.

268
00:23:00.733 --> 00:23:02.200
JAKE.

269
00:23:02.267 --> 00:23:05.633
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG
WITH THIS PLACE.

270
00:23:05.700 --> 00:23:08.933
NOT THE ELECTRICITY
AGAIN?

271
00:23:09.067 --> 00:23:11.667
NO. IT'S NOT THAT.

272
00:23:11.733 --> 00:23:15.700
JAKE. I DON'T THINK
I CAN LIVE HERE.

273
00:23:15.767 --> 00:23:17.067
OH. NO.

274
00:23:17.100 --> 00:23:21.867
LOOK. HONEY. I KNOW THERE'S BEEN
A LOT OF REPAIRS LATELY.

275
00:23:21.933 --> 00:23:23.533
BUT THAT'LL END.

276
00:23:23.600 --> 00:23:25.333
I JUST DON'T FEEL SAFE.

277
00:23:25.400 --> 00:23:28.833
AND I DON'T THINK THE GIRLS
FEEL SAFE. EITHER.

278
00:23:28.900 --> 00:23:32.267
WELL...I CAN GET
AN ALARM SYSTEM. IF YOU WANT.

279
00:23:32.333 --> 00:23:36.267
I DON'T WANT AN ALARM SYSTEM.
I WANT A DIFFERENT HOUSE.

280
00:23:36.333 --> 00:23:38.633
OH. CINDY. CINDY. COME ON.

281
00:23:38.700 --> 00:23:42.200
DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.
WE JUST MOVED IN.

282
00:23:42.267 --> 00:23:44.733
Cindy: HOW CAN I TELL SOMEBODY
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE

283
00:23:44.800 --> 00:23:47.833
WHEN IT'S SO BIZARRE. EVERYTHING
THAT WAS HAPPENING. YOU KNOW?

284
00:23:47.900 --> 00:23:49.700
WHO'S GONNA BELIEVE IT?

285
00:23:49.767 --> 00:23:52.267
YOU KNOW
WE CAN'T AFFORD IT.

286
00:23:55.067 --> 00:23:59.333
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT TOO THRILLED
WITH THE HOUSE.

287
00:23:59.400 --> 00:24:02.533
BUT JUST GIVE IT SOME TIME.

288
00:24:02.600 --> 00:24:04.233
PLEASE?

289
00:24:04.300 --> 00:24:07.767
I DON'T THINK I CAN.

290
00:24:07.833 --> 00:24:09.367
FINE.

291
00:24:09.433 --> 00:24:11.767
PLEASE FILL ME IN
ON HOW YOU PLAN

292
00:24:11.833 --> 00:24:13.800
TO COME UP WITH
ALL THIS MONEY!

293
00:24:13.867 --> 00:24:15.833
I DON'T KNOW!
BUT I'LL FIGURE IT OUT!

294
00:24:27.567 --> 00:24:30.333
Brooke: THAT UPSET ME. BECAUSE
WHEN WE LIVED IN BELLEVILLE.

295
00:24:30.400 --> 00:24:31.800
THEY ALWAYS GOT ALONG.

296
00:24:31.867 --> 00:24:34.467
AND NOW IT SEEMED THAT MY MOTHER
AND FATHER WERE FIGHTING A LOT.

297
00:24:34.533 --> 00:24:36.633
COME ON. GIRLS.

298
00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:55.400
Narrator: WEEKS PASS.

299
00:24:55.467 --> 00:24:58.433
AND THE STRANGE ACTIVITY
CONTINUES.

300
00:25:02.533 --> 00:25:05.300
ALTHOUGH CINDY IS NOT
A RELIGIOUS PERSON.

301
00:25:05.367 --> 00:25:08.067
SHE BEGINS TO PRAY
ON A REGULAR BASIS.

302
00:25:23.067 --> 00:25:27.067
SHE WONDERS IF SHE CAN
FIND COMFORT IN HER FAITH.

303
00:25:30.133 --> 00:25:34.567
Cindy:
I PUT UP A PICTURE OF JESUS.

304
00:25:34.633 --> 00:25:37.400
I FELT LIKE THAT WAS PROTECTION
FOR US.

305
00:25:41.133 --> 00:25:43.067
CINDY?

306
00:25:44.633 --> 00:25:46.067
CINDY. COME HERE.

307
00:25:50.533 --> 00:25:52.467
WHAT IS IT. JAKE?

308
00:25:57.533 --> 00:25:59.233
JAKE?

309
00:26:26.267 --> 00:26:27.767
[ GASPING ]

310
00:26:30.967 --> 00:26:34.667
[ CRYING ]

311
00:26:34.733 --> 00:26:54.933
I WAS SCARED HALF TO DEATH.

312
00:26:55.067 --> 00:26:57.067
CINDY. ARE YOU OKAY?

313
00:26:57.133 --> 00:26:59.233
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

314
00:26:59.300 --> 00:27:01.567
DID YOU HURT YOURSELF?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

315
00:27:01.633 --> 00:27:03.867
SOMETHING ATTACKED ME.
AND THEN I COULDN'T BREATHE!

316
00:27:03.933 --> 00:27:06.267
OKAY. SLOW DOWN. SLOW DOWN.
TAKE A DEEP BREATH.

317
00:27:06.333 --> 00:27:07.467
TELL ME.

318
00:27:09.900 --> 00:27:11.833
THERE'S A GHOST
IN THIS HOUSE.

319
00:27:11.900 --> 00:27:14.933
COME ON. HONEY.
TELL ME THE TRUTH.

320
00:27:15.067 --> 00:27:17.600
TELL ME WHAT HAPPENED.
NO. I'M BEING SERIOUS. JAKE.

321
00:27:17.667 --> 00:27:20.133
THERE'S SOMETHING HERE.
AND IT'S TRYING TO HURT ME.

322
00:27:20.200 --> 00:27:21.667
SWEETIE. IT'S JUST US.

323
00:27:21.733 --> 00:27:23.900
IT'S JUST
IN YOUR IMAGINATION.

324
00:27:23.967 --> 00:27:25.633
NO. YOU'RE NOT LISTENING
TO ME!

325
00:27:25.700 --> 00:27:28.600
THERE'S SOMETHING IN THIS HOUSE.
AND IT'S TRYING TO KILL ME.

326
00:27:28.667 --> 00:27:30.133
AND YOU DON'T EVEN CARE!

327
00:27:30.200 --> 00:27:33.500
OF COURSE I CARE. BUT TRY
TO BE REASONABLE HERE. CINDY.

328
00:27:33.567 --> 00:27:36.700
THERE'S NOTHING
IN THIS HOUSE.

329
00:27:36.767 --> 00:27:38.333
I CAN'T LIVE HERE.

330
00:27:38.400 --> 00:27:41.167
JAKE. IT TRIED
TO SUFFOCATE ME!

331
00:27:41.233 --> 00:27:42.267
CINDY...

332
00:27:42.333 --> 00:27:44.067
[ SIGHS ]

333
00:27:44.067 --> 00:27:46.667
THIS HOUSE
IS NOT HAUNTED. OKAY?

334
00:27:46.733 --> 00:27:49.067
GHOSTS DO NOT EXIST.

335
00:27:49.133 --> 00:27:51.700
[ Crying ] I WISH I NEVER
LET YOU CONVINCE ME

336
00:27:51.767 --> 00:27:52.833
TO BUY THIS HOUSE.

337
00:27:52.900 --> 00:27:54.367
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

338
00:27:54.433 --> 00:27:57.467
YOU WANTED THIS HOUSE
AS MUCH AS I DID!

339
00:27:57.533 --> 00:28:00.100
WHAT'S GOTTEN
INTO YOU LATELY?

340
00:28:00.167 --> 00:28:01.533
JAKE. I'M SCARED!

341
00:28:01.600 --> 00:28:04.733
WE SUNK OUR LIFE SAVINGS
INTO THIS HOUSE!

342
00:28:04.800 --> 00:28:08.500
WE ARE NOT MOVING.
AND THAT'S FINAL.

343
00:28:08.567 --> 00:28:10.433
Cindy:
I COULDN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE.

344
00:28:10.500 --> 00:28:12.733
I NEEDED HELP.

345
00:28:28.300 --> 00:28:31.067
I STARTED CALLING
DIFFERENT CHURCHES.

346
00:28:31.100 --> 00:28:33.500
AND NOBODY WANTED TO HELP ME.

347
00:28:33.567 --> 00:28:38.667
FINALLY. I SPOKE WITH A PRIEST.
AND HE WAS GOING TO HELP ME.

348
00:28:38.733 --> 00:28:41.467
Narrator: IN THE NEARBY TOWN
OF BELLEVILLE...

349
00:28:41.533 --> 00:28:43.600
MY LIFE'S FALLING APART.
FATHER.

350
00:28:43.667 --> 00:28:45.900
I JUST DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

351
00:28:45.967 --> 00:28:48.200
...CINDY MEETS
WITH FATHER THOMAS.

352
00:28:48.267 --> 00:28:49.800
FROM WHAT YOU'VE TOLD ME.

353
00:28:49.867 --> 00:28:53.100
IT APPEARS AS THOUGH
IT MAY BE DEMONIC.

354
00:28:54.967 --> 00:28:56.733
THE FIRST STEP
IS TO BLESS THE HOUSE.

355
00:28:56.800 --> 00:28:58.167
THAT MAY DRIVE THE DEMON OUT.

356
00:28:59.267 --> 00:29:01.167
BUT I'LL NEED SOME TIME
TO PREPARE.

357
00:29:01.233 --> 00:29:02.833
I'LL HAVE TO FAST AND PRAY

358
00:29:02.900 --> 00:29:05.633
BEFORE I CAN ACTUALLY
CONDUCT THE BLESSING.

359
00:29:05.700 --> 00:29:07.200
I UNDERSTAND. FATHER.

360
00:29:07.267 --> 00:29:09.200
I'M SO GRATEFUL
FOR YOUR HELP.

361
00:29:11.600 --> 00:29:13.533
HERE.

362
00:29:13.600 --> 00:29:18.933
WHEN YOU'RE AFRAID.
READ PSALM 91.

363
00:29:19.067 --> 00:29:21.433
IT WILL PROTECT YOU
FROM EVIL.

364
00:29:21.500 --> 00:29:23.300
THANK YOU AGAIN. FATHER.

365
00:29:36.200 --> 00:29:41.100
THAT NIGHT. CINDY ANXIOUSLY
WAITS FOR JAKE TO COME HOME.

366
00:29:41.167 --> 00:29:44.633
SHE KEEPS HERSELF CALM
BY READING THE BIBLE.

367
00:29:44.700 --> 00:29:47.167
[ GRAVEL CRUNCHES ]

368
00:30:20.567 --> 00:30:22.500
JAKE?

369
00:30:43.633 --> 00:30:45.133
[ SCREAMS ]

370
00:30:52.500 --> 00:30:54.067
PLEASE HURRY!

371
00:31:03.633 --> 00:31:05.467
[ SCREAMING ]

372
00:31:05.533 --> 00:31:06.733
[ SCREAMS ]

373
00:31:19.400 --> 00:31:21.600
[ SIREN WAILS ]

374
00:31:21.667 --> 00:31:24.800
POLICE DEPARTMENT!
PUT THE AX DOWN!

375
00:31:24.867 --> 00:31:27.600
Cindy: I WAS RELIEVED TO SEE
THE POLICE WHEN THEY CAME.

376
00:31:27.667 --> 00:31:28.933
IT WAS LIKE. "THANK GOD."

377
00:31:29.067 --> 00:31:30.733
PUT YOUR HANDS
BEHIND YOUR HEAD.

378
00:31:30.800 --> 00:31:32.900
HE HAD CHOPPED THE DOOR DOWN
WITH THE AX.

379
00:31:32.967 --> 00:31:35.067
THANK GOD THEY MADE IT IN TIME

380
00:31:35.067 --> 00:31:38.467
BEFORE HE DID
WHATEVER HE WAS OUT TO DO.

381
00:31:38.533 --> 00:31:40.367
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

382
00:31:50.567 --> 00:31:54.067
ARE YOU OKAY?

383
00:31:54.133 --> 00:31:57.833
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED HERE?

384
00:31:57.900 --> 00:32:00.167
JAKE...

385
00:32:00.233 --> 00:32:04.467
I DON'T KNOW. HE JUST --
HE DIDN'T LOOK RIGHT.

386
00:32:04.533 --> 00:32:09.067
Narrator: CINDY BELIEVES
THAT JAKE WAS POSSESSED.

387
00:32:09.133 --> 00:32:12.167
DO YOU WANT TO
TAKE CHARGES OUT ON HIM?

388
00:32:12.233 --> 00:32:15.633
SHE NOW KNOWS IT WAS JAKE
WHO TRIED TO SUFFOCATE HER.

389
00:32:17.733 --> 00:32:19.800
MA'AM?

390
00:32:19.867 --> 00:32:22.067
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

391
00:32:22.067 --> 00:32:24.367
CINDY DOES NOT PRESS CHARGES.

392
00:32:24.433 --> 00:32:28.067
BELIEVING THAT JAKE'S WILL
WAS NOT HIS OWN.

393
00:32:29.867 --> 00:32:32.833
BUT SHE DOES NOT ALLOW HIM
BACK INTO THE HOUSE.

394
00:32:32.900 --> 00:32:36.333
HE MOVES IN WITH HIS MOTHER.

395
00:32:46.867 --> 00:32:50.333
AN HOUR LATER. THE GIRLS RETURN
FROM THEIR MOVIE.

396
00:32:54.800 --> 00:32:58.333
WHAT HAPPENED
TO THE DOOR. MOM?

397
00:33:00.633 --> 00:33:03.167
WHAT'S WRONG. MOM?

398
00:33:04.633 --> 00:33:07.633
DADDY'S GONNA HAVE TO GO AWAY
FOR A WHILE.

399
00:33:07.700 --> 00:33:09.100
WHY?

400
00:33:09.167 --> 00:33:12.567
IT'S REALLY COMPLICATED.
BUT I'M TRYING TO FIX THINGS.

401
00:33:12.633 --> 00:33:16.233
AND MAYBE IN A FEW WEEKS.
THINGS WILL BE NORMAL AGAIN.

402
00:33:16.300 --> 00:33:17.733
DAD'S NOT GONNA BE HERE
AT ALL?

403
00:33:17.800 --> 00:33:20.067
Brooke: WHEN I FOUND OUT THAT
MY DAD WASN'T GONNA BE AROUND.

404
00:33:20.067 --> 00:33:22.967
I WAS REALLY UPSET
BECAUSE WE WERE REALLY CLOSE.

405
00:33:23.067 --> 00:33:26.267
AND IT JUST SEEMED LIKE
SINCE WE MOVED INTO THE HOUSE.

406
00:33:26.333 --> 00:33:28.433
OUR WHOLE FAMILY
WAS FALLING APART.

407
00:33:28.500 --> 00:33:31.567
DON'T YOU WORRY.
EVERYTHING IS GONNA BE FINE.

408
00:33:31.633 --> 00:33:33.933
I PROMISE.

409
00:33:34.067 --> 00:33:35.267
NOW GO WASH UP.

410
00:33:35.333 --> 00:33:38.733
I'LL BE UP IN A FEW MINUTES
TO TUCK YOU IN.

411
00:33:38.800 --> 00:33:40.367
OKAY.

412
00:33:50.667 --> 00:33:52.933
[ SOBBING ]

413
00:34:16.400 --> 00:34:17.633
[ SCREAMS ]

414
00:34:19.433 --> 00:34:22.767
Narrator:
CINDY AND THE GIRLS FLEE TO
ANITA'S ONE-BEDROOM APARTMENT.

415
00:34:24.500 --> 00:34:27.467
[ Crying ] IT POSSESSED JAKE.
AND HE TRIED TO ATTACK ME.

416
00:34:31.367 --> 00:34:32.533
I CAN'T GO BACK THERE!

417
00:34:32.600 --> 00:34:34.100
WHAT IF IT TRIES
TO HURT THE GIRLS?

418
00:34:34.167 --> 00:34:37.200
I WAS SO RELIEVED
THAT THEY WERE SAFE...

419
00:34:38.900 --> 00:34:41.267
...AND THAT WE WEREN'T
GOING BACK TO THE HOUSE.

420
00:34:44.400 --> 00:34:48.067
"THE LORD IS MY REFUGE
AND MY FORTRESS.

421
00:34:48.067 --> 00:34:50.267
"MY GOD. IN WHOM I TRUST.

422
00:34:50.333 --> 00:34:53.700
"I WILL NOT FEAR THE TERROR
THAT ATTACKS BY NIGHT.

423
00:34:53.767 --> 00:34:55.833
"OR THE ARROW THAT FLIES BY DAY.

424
00:34:55.900 --> 00:34:58.367
"NO AFFLICTION
WILL ENTER MY HOUSE.

425
00:34:58.433 --> 00:35:02.133
HE WILL GIVE HIS ANGELS REIGN
OVER ME TO KEEP ME SAFE."

426
00:35:02.200 --> 00:35:05.200
WHEN I STARTED RECITING
PSALMS 91.

427
00:35:05.267 --> 00:35:08.300
I FELT LIKE I WAS
BEING PROTECTED.

428
00:35:08.367 --> 00:35:12.333
LIKE GOD WAS WITH ME
AND HE WAS GONNA HELP ME.

429
00:35:35.333 --> 00:35:37.100
THE NEXT THING I KNOW.

430
00:35:37.167 --> 00:35:41.067
THERE'S NO HOUSE THERE
WHERE MY HOUSE SHOULD'VE BEEN.

431
00:35:41.067 --> 00:35:43.133
I DIDN'T UNDERSTAND IT.

432
00:35:43.200 --> 00:35:45.333
I JUST THINK I WAS
IN A DIFFERENT TIME.

433
00:35:45.400 --> 00:35:47.200
[ MAN CHANTING ]

434
00:35:59.267 --> 00:36:01.200
IT WAS AN ANSWER TO MY PRAYER.

435
00:36:01.267 --> 00:36:25.567
TELLING ME THAT SOMETHING HAD
WENT ON YEARS AND YEARS AGO.

436
00:36:25.633 --> 00:36:27.067
Narrator: THE NEXT DAY.

437
00:36:27.100 --> 00:36:30.133
CINDY GOES TO FATHER THOMAS
TO TELL HIM ABOUT HER DREAM.

438
00:36:30.200 --> 00:36:32.433
THESE MEN
WERE PERFORMING A CEREMONY

439
00:36:32.500 --> 00:36:35.067
THAT HAD SOMETHING
TO DO WITH THE DEAD.

440
00:36:36.633 --> 00:36:40.067
THEY WERE DIGGING UP A BODY
WHERE MY HOUSE NOW STANDS.

441
00:36:43.900 --> 00:36:45.333
IT SOUNDS AS THOUGH
YOU WITNESSED

442
00:36:45.400 --> 00:36:47.300
A RITUAL OF NECROMANCY.

443
00:36:47.367 --> 00:36:50.867
THAT'S A FORM OF SUMMONING
A SPIRIT. A DEMON.

444
00:36:50.933 --> 00:36:53.700
OR A HUMAN SOUL
TO ENTER A CORPSE.

445
00:36:53.767 --> 00:36:55.967
BUT WHY?

446
00:36:56.067 --> 00:36:58.467
WELL.
THERE'S SEVERAL REASONS.

447
00:36:58.533 --> 00:37:01.867
BUT MAINLY. THE GOAL
IS TO CONJURE UP A DEMON.

448
00:37:01.933 --> 00:37:05.300
WHICH EXPLAINS THE DEMONIC
PRESENCE IN YOUR HOME.

449
00:37:06.300 --> 00:37:10.367
I'LL BE ABLE TO PERFORM
THE HOUSE BLESSING TOMORROW.

450
00:37:10.433 --> 00:37:12.067
THANK YOU.

451
00:37:12.133 --> 00:37:14.533
BUT...

452
00:37:14.600 --> 00:37:17.267
I'M GOING TO ASK YOU TO DO
SOMETHING YOU MAY NOT LIKE.

453
00:37:17.333 --> 00:37:20.433
ANYTHING. FATHER.
I JUST WANT THIS TO END.

454
00:37:20.500 --> 00:37:23.067
I NEED YOU AND THE GIRLS
TO BE PRESENT

455
00:37:23.133 --> 00:37:25.100
WHILE I PERFORM THE BLESSING.

456
00:37:27.267 --> 00:37:29.967
YOU MUST CONFRONT THE DEMON

457
00:37:30.067 --> 00:37:34.067
IN ORDER TO SEND HIM
TO THE OTHER SIDE.

458
00:37:35.700 --> 00:37:39.367
WELL...I GUESS I HAVE
NO OTHER CHOICE.

459
00:37:39.433 --> 00:37:41.933
I REALLY DIDN'T WANT ANY OF US
IN THE HOUSE.

460
00:37:42.067 --> 00:37:45.233
I WOULD'VE MUCH RATHER HANDED
HIM THE KEY AND LET HIM DO IT.

461
00:37:45.300 --> 00:37:47.367
BUT IT COULDN'T BE DONE
THAT WAY.

462
00:37:53.367 --> 00:37:55.500
Narrator:
FATHER THOMAS KNOWS

463
00:37:55.567 --> 00:37:58.167
THAT A DEMON
IS HIGHLY UNPREDICTABLE.

464
00:37:58.233 --> 00:38:01.800
IT HAS ALREADY MANIFESTED ITSELF
IN DIFFERENT WAYS.

465
00:38:11.200 --> 00:38:13.367
HI. FATHER THOMAS.

466
00:38:13.433 --> 00:38:14.533
HELLO.

467
00:38:33.367 --> 00:38:36.133
PEACE BE IN THIS HOUSE
AND WITH ALL WHO LIVE HERE.

468
00:38:37.167 --> 00:38:39.067
LORD GOD OF HEAVEN AND EARTH.

469
00:38:39.133 --> 00:38:41.867
BLESS THIS HOUSE
AND ALL WHO INHABIT IT.

470
00:38:41.933 --> 00:38:45.067
Cindy: I WAS STILL SCARED.
BUT I KEPT PRAYING.

471
00:38:45.067 --> 00:38:47.100
I DIDN'T WANT ANYBODY HURT.

472
00:38:47.167 --> 00:38:50.267
AND I JUST WANTED THIS
TO BE OVER WITH.

473
00:38:50.333 --> 00:38:54.733
IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER
AND THE SON AND THE HOLY SPIRIT.

474
00:38:54.800 --> 00:38:56.967
LORD GOD OF HEAVEN AND EARTH.

475
00:38:57.067 --> 00:39:00.300
BLESS THIS HOUSE
AND ALL WHO INHABIT IT.

476
00:39:00.367 --> 00:39:02.433
FILL THEM
WITH THE LIGHT OF CHRIST

477
00:39:02.500 --> 00:39:06.300
THAT THEIR CONCERNS FOR OTHERS
MAY REFLECT YOUR LOVE.

478
00:39:06.367 --> 00:39:08.467
WE ASK THROUGH CHRIST OUR LORD

479
00:39:08.533 --> 00:39:12.800
IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER
AND THE SON AND THE HOLY SPIRIT.

480
00:39:12.867 --> 00:39:15.867
FILL THEM
WITH THE LIGHT OF CHRIST

481
00:39:15.933 --> 00:39:19.133
THAT THEIR CONCERNS FOR OTHERS
MAY REFLECT YOUR LOVE.

482
00:39:19.200 --> 00:39:21.833
WE ASK THROUGH CHRIST OUR LORD

483
00:39:21.900 --> 00:39:25.633
IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER
AND THE SON AND THE HOLY SPIRIT.

484
00:39:30.467 --> 00:39:32.333
I CAN'T THANK YOU ENOUGH.
FATHER.

485
00:39:32.400 --> 00:39:33.500
OF COURSE. MY DEAR.

486
00:39:33.567 --> 00:39:36.100
I'LL ALWAYS BE HERE FOR YOU
IN YOUR TIME OF NEED.

487
00:39:36.167 --> 00:39:37.600
THANK YOU.

488
00:39:41.133 --> 00:39:43.100
GOODBYE.

489
00:39:47.433 --> 00:39:51.800
I FELT RELIEVED
THAT WE FINALLY HAD OUR HOUSE

490
00:39:51.867 --> 00:39:54.133
AND THERE WAS NO EVIL.

491
00:40:01.133 --> 00:40:02.467
Narrator: THAT NIGHT.

492
00:40:02.533 --> 00:40:05.567
CINDY AND THE GIRLS
MOVE BACK INTO THE HOUSE.

493
00:40:22.367 --> 00:40:25.533
I FELT MY HAIR RISE ON MY NECK.

494
00:40:38.467 --> 00:40:40.300
SOMETHING GRABBED ME.

495
00:40:41.800 --> 00:40:43.300
MOM!

496
00:40:46.367 --> 00:40:47.767
[ SCREAMS ]

497
00:40:47.833 --> 00:40:48.967
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

498
00:40:49.033 --> 00:40:49.967
WHAT?!

499
00:40:50.033 --> 00:40:51.133
MOM -- BROOKE!

500
00:40:51.200 --> 00:40:53.000
[ GASPS ]

501
00:40:53.067 --> 00:40:54.333
NO!

502
00:40:54.400 --> 00:40:56.033
YOU CAN'T HAVE MY DAUGHTER!

503
00:40:56.100 --> 00:40:59.667
IN THE NAME OF THE LORD.
LET MY DAUGHTER GO!

504
00:40:59.733 --> 00:41:01.133
[ SCREAMS ]

505
00:41:01.200 --> 00:41:04.100
[ Crying ] OH. MY GOD!
OH. MY GOD!

506
00:41:04.167 --> 00:41:05.933
OH. MY GOD. MY BABY!

507
00:41:06.067 --> 00:41:08.233
OH. THANK YOU. GOD.

508
00:41:08.300 --> 00:41:09.600
I WAS TERRIFIED.

509
00:41:09.667 --> 00:41:13.333
I'VE NEVER. EVER SEEN ANYTHING
SO POWERFUL IN MY LIFE.

510
00:41:13.400 --> 00:41:16.300
GIRLS. COME ON. COME ON!
COME ON. HONEY. COME ON!

511
00:41:16.367 --> 00:41:20.200
COME ON. RUN! HURRY!
HURRY. HONEY! GO!

512
00:41:20.267 --> 00:41:23.333
RUN. HONEY!
COME ON. COME ON!

513
00:41:23.400 --> 00:41:27.100
COME ON. GIRLS.
LET'S JUST GO. GO. GO. GO. GO!

514
00:41:27.167 --> 00:41:28.633
JUST GO. GIRLS!

515
00:41:31.067 --> 00:41:32.833
[ CRYING ]

516
00:41:35.800 --> 00:41:39.667
I DON'T KNOW. I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW. I DON'T KNOW!

517
00:41:39.733 --> 00:41:41.100
I DON'T KNOW!

518
00:41:45.267 --> 00:41:47.067
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

519
00:42:03.100 --> 00:42:06.267
Narrator: CINDY AND THE GIRLS
STAY WITH HER MOTHER

520
00:42:06.333 --> 00:42:08.400
WHILE SHE TRIES
TO SELL THE HOUSE.

521
00:42:12.700 --> 00:42:16.433
CINDY AND JAKE ARE UNABLE
TO BRIDGE THE RIFT BETWEEN THEM

522
00:42:16.500 --> 00:42:19.167
AND DECIDE TO GO
THEIR SEPARATE WAYS.

523
00:42:20.733 --> 00:42:23.067
CINDY BEGINS WORKING
AT A LOCAL HOTEL

524
00:42:23.100 --> 00:42:27.733
AND EVENTUALLY SAVES ENOUGH
MONEY TO PURCHASE A NEW HOME.

525
00:42:27.800 --> 00:42:31.433
JAKE MAINTAINS A RELATIONSHIP
WITH BROOKE AND CHRISTIE.

526
00:42:31.500 --> 00:42:34.967
SEEING THEM ON WEEKENDS.

527
00:42:35.067 --> 00:42:38.067
OVER TIME.
CINDY AND HER DAUGHTERS' LIVES

528
00:42:38.100 --> 00:42:40.500
BECOME PEACEFUL ONCE MORE.

529
00:42:40.567 --> 00:42:45.467
BUT MEMORIES OF THEIR HORRIFYING
ORDEAL CONTINUE TO HAUNT THEM.

530
00:42:45.533 --> 00:42:48.567
Cindy:
GOING THROUGH THIS EXPERIENCE

531
00:42:48.633 --> 00:42:52.333
MADE ME BELIEVE
THAT THERE IS EVIL OUT HERE.

532
00:42:54.433 --> 00:42:57.800
WE HAVE NIGHTMARES STILL.
15 YEARS LATER.

533
00:42:57.867 --> 00:42:59.800
IT'LL ALWAYS BE WITH US.

534
00:42:59.867 --> 00:43:03.433
BUT WE'RE GETTING STRONGER
ABOUT THINGS.

535
00:43:08.167 --> 00:43:11.733
Narrator: THE HOUSE REMAINS
EMPTY FOR QUITE SOME TIME

536
00:43:11.800 --> 00:43:15.067
UNTIL A COUPLE FROM OUT OF TOWN
BUYS THE PLACE.

537
00:43:15.067 --> 00:43:16.633
WITHIN A FEW MONTHS.

538
00:43:16.700 --> 00:43:20.067
THEIR DAUGHTER ENCOUNTERS
AN EVIL PRESENCE

539
00:43:20.067 --> 00:43:23.600
AND THE FAMILY
QUICKLY MOVES OUT.

540
00:43:23.667 --> 00:43:26.600
